            <biogHist>
                <p>Peter Morrison (he appears to be called Roderick Morrison in the 1841 census) was
                    born c1800 in Aird, Benbecula; his parents were Donald Morrison, crofter, and
                    Ann Morrison née MacPherson. He worked as a farmer/crofter in Balivanich,
                    Benbecula and was married to Flora or Flory MacDonald née MacDonald. In the 1851
                    census their children are listed as Donald (20), John (18), James (15), Ann
                    [Anne] (13), Effy (11), Christena [Christy, Christina, Chirsty] (8), Catherine
                    (3) and Marione [Marion] (6 months). A birth certificate for another daughter,
                    Henrica, exists from 1840 but as she does not appear in a census it is likely
                    that she died in infancy. In the 1861 census, Peter and Flora are found in
                    Balivanich with their son John, shoemaker, and four of their daughters.</p>
                <p>Peter Morrison died in February 1881 in Balivanich with his daughter Chirsty
                    present. </p>
